  <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
   <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
   <p>A weekly gay entertainment guide for New York City, 1991 to July 10, 2009, HX, titled Homo
    Xtra for a while, was available for free in bars and other locations, concentrated in the West
    Village and Chelsea and, during the summer, in the Pines and Cherry Grove. Its slogan was: "The
    totally biased, politically incorrect party paper".</p>
  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
   <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
   <p>Organizational files from the co-publisher Matthew Blank.</p>
